                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.21/478: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Philip</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-02T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 2, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received August 4, 4.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>108. Colombian Foreign Office and press announce that treaty will be discussed by
                    Senate in open session Tuesday the 5th instant. I respectfully suggest that
                    steps should be taken to avoid discussion of confidential agreement and note of
                    Colombian Government signifying acceptance of modifications which I obtained for
                    information of committee only. President in agreeing to publication of the note
                    stipulated that it would be subsidiary [to] ratification in [<hi rend="italic"
                        >of</hi>] treaty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Philip</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
